09. Operators
     a. Arithmetic Operators => 1.+, 2.-, 3.*, 4./, 5.%, 6.**
     b. Comparison Operators => 1.==, 2.!=, 3.>, 4.>=, 5.<, 6.<=, 7.<=>, 8.===, 9..eql? 10.equal?
     c. Assignment Operators => 1.=, 2.+=, 3.-=, 4.*=, 5./=, 6.%=, 7.**=
     d. Parallel Assignment => a,b,c=1,2,3 a=b=c a,b = b,a
     e. Bitwise Operators => | binary or, & binary and, ^ binary xor, ~ binary ones complement, << binary left shift, >> binary right shift
     f. Logical Operators => or ||, and &&, not !
     g. Ternary Operator a=b ? (puts true) : (puts false)
     h. Range Operators
        Ranges as Sequences, Ranges as Conditions, Ranges as Intervals
     i. defined? Operators
     j. Dot "." and Double Colon "::" Operators
